olive oil
1 tbs honey
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 Cucumber
1 Tomato
1 packet Halloumi
1 sachet Lemon Pepper Seasoning
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Slice cucumber into thin sticks. Thinly slice tomato into wedges.
• Cut halloumi into 1cm-thick slices.
• In a small bowl, combine lemon pepper spice blend, the honey and a splash of water.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook halloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add lemon pepper mixture and turn to coat.

• Meanwhile, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season and set aside.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a microwave-safe plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Build your tacos by topping tortillas with tomato salad, cucumber and lemon pepper halloumi.
• Drizzle over Greek-style yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!